cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with the task of retrieving relevant video moments from a large corpus of untrimmed, unsegmented videos given a natural language query. This involves aligning features for a natural language query to a sequence of short video clips that compose a candidate moment in a video. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques, which makes cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves multimedia processing and machine learning techniques, which makes cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible sub-categories.
